Dragonfly Navigator
-------------------
A simple and efficient file manager for Linux/KDE.

Installing and running on Kubuntu
---------------------------------
Download .deb file from the release page. Then install like this:
$ sudo dpkg -i dragonfly_xxx.deb
$ sudo apt install -f

Run:
$ dragonfly 
(or find it via the application menu)


Non-debian/ubuntu based setups:
Download the .tar.gz binary release from the release page. Then install like this:

If you get an error on loading HEIC/HEIF image files, make sure you install libheif from your distribution.

Make sure you read the help text (press help button) since Dragonfly Navigator has some caveats and tricks you need to know in order to use it efficiently.

Building and running from sources
---------------------------------
Prerequisites (ubuntu/debian):

1. Install basic prerequisites for running
$ sudo apt install libheif1

2. Install prerequisites for building the openwith binary
$ sudo apt install pyqt5-dev-tools qtcreator libkf5-dev libkdeframeworks5-dev libkf5widgetsaddons-dev libkf5xmlgui-dev libkf5textwidgets-dev libkf5kio-dev build-essential libkf5config-dev libkdecorations2-dev libqt5x11extras5-dev qtdeclarative5-dev extra-cmake-modules libkf5guiaddons-dev libkf5configwidgets-dev libkf5windowsystem-dev libkf5coreaddons-dev gettext

3.Building:
$ cd src
$ ./build

4. Run:
$ ./dragonfly

To edit the GUI files: Install qtcreator and use that to edit the UI (.ui files). 
$ sudo apt install pyqt5-dev-tools qtcreator
$ qtcreator mainwin.ui (for example)

Third party packages included with this software
------------------------------------------------

1. pyheif https://github.com/carsales/pyheif
2. inotify_simple https://github.com/chrisjbillington/inotify_simple
3. exifread https://github.com/ianare/exif-py
